The paper deals with graph colorings and uses algorithmic techniques to prove upper bounds on various chromatic numbers and indices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS), which further support the likelihood of these sub-categories. The paper also involves probabilistic methods and information theory, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
